All Implemented Interfaces:
Pipe<I,I>, Node, Sink<I>, Source<I>, MetaDataManageable<Object,Object>, MetaDataProvider<CompositeMetaData<Object,Object>>
public class Logger<I>
extends Mapper<I,I>

A special kind of a Mapper that applies an unary print-function to each incoming element that writes this element's string representation to a user-defined PrintStream.

Since:
1.1

Logger

public Logger(Source<? extends I> source,
              int ID,
              PrintStream printStream,
              boolean println)
Creates a new Logger as an internal component of a query graph.
The subscription to the specified source is fulfilled immediately.

Parameters:
source - This pipe gets subscribed to the specified source.
ID - This pipe uses the given ID for subscription.
printStream - The PrintStream the elements' string representation is forwarded to.
println - If true the elements' string representation is separted by a CR/LF, otherwise not.

Logger

public Logger(Source<? extends I> source,
              PrintStream printStream,
              boolean println)
Creates a new Logger as an internal component of a query graph.
The subscription to the specified source is fulfilled immediately. The DEFAULT_ID is used for subscription.

Parameters:
source - This pipe gets subscribed to the specified source.
printStream - The PrintStream the elements' string representation is forwarded to.
println - If true the elements' string representation is separted by a CR/LF, otherwise not.

Logger

public Logger(Source<? extends I> source,
              boolean println)
Creates a new Logger as an internal component of a query graph.
The subscription to the specified source is fulfilled immediately. The DEFAULT_ID is used for subscription. The input rate and the output rate are not measured.
All incoming elements are printed to Java's standard output stream System.out.

Parameters:
source - This pipe gets subscribed to the specified source.
println - If true the elements' string representation is separted by a CR/LF, otherwise not.

Logger

public Logger(Source<? extends I> source)
Creates a new Logger as an internal component of a query graph.
The subscription to the specified source is fulfilled immediately. The DEFAULT_ID is used for subscription. The input rate and the output rate are not measured.
All incoming elements are printed to Java's standard output stream System.out and separated by a CR/LF.

Parameters:
source - This pipe gets subscribed to the specified source.
